# After changes — deploy, sync, restart?

When you finish **substantive** work (app code, `app/templates`, DB/migrations, `VERSION`, installer/packaging, service config, CI workflows, or anything that affects the **running** Grabby build), **end your reply** with a **short, explicit check-in** for the user:

> **Want to deploy this build and sync your machine?**  
> I can help with: **install new `GrabbySetup.exe` / restart the Windows service** (8765), **`git pull`** (or match **`origin/master`**), and **restart the dev server** (`scripts/dev-start.ps1`, 8766) so the UI and DB migrations match the repo.

- **Ask once per task** (not after every tiny edit in the same turn).
- **Skip** for **trivial-only** changes (e.g. comment typos, pure internal refactors with no runtime effect) unless they’re validating that area.
- If they **yes** / **do it**: propose **concrete** PowerShell/git steps (or run them if they want terminal actions). For **full release + local**, follow **`.cursor/rules/bump-and-restart-workflow.mdc`**.
- If they **no** / **later**: acknowledge — they can come back when ready.

**Goal:** They’re never left wondering whether to redeploy, pull, or restart to see the fix.
